Description: Glazed composition shabti of a woman named Mety with a blue lappet-wig, a red modelled face with traced brown features, a beige body, a brown collar and parallel red hands in relief holding two brown hoes; the front of the leg section is inscribed with a column of brown Hieroglyphs; the back is decorated with a representation of a brown seed-basket.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
